I Want to Be Your Dog

description: Acclaimed cartoonist Chris Ware reveals the outtakes of his genius in these intimate, imaginative, and whimsical sketches collected from the years during which he completed his award-winning graphic novel Jimmy Corrigan: The Smartest Kid on Earth. His novel not only won the Manchester Guardian First Novel prize in 2001 but it has sold over 100,000 copies. This book is as much a companion volume to Jimmy Corrigan - one of the great crossover success stories - as a tremendous art collection from of one of America's most interesting and popular graphic artists.
name: Volume  One

volume.name: Metal Men of Mars & Other Improbable Tales

description: The Complete Wash Tubbs and Captain Easy by Roy Crane were published by the Flying Buttress Classics Library. Widely considered to be one of the first great adventure strips, Wash Tubbs the wise-cracking, girl-chasing opportunist and soldier of fortune Captain Easy are back for more fun and adventure. Volume 14 (1938-1939) reprints Crane's classic comic strips. Wash attempts to win back the hand of Carol McKee. Plus, Wash and Easy must stay one step ahead of a gang of cut-throat pirates, the affections of Amazon Bessie, and the enemies of their pet swink.

description: Shine your tow cables up and put your snow tires on, the Derby is on! Mater squares off against his long-time nemesis Bubba the tow truck in the Rust Bucket Derby. Mater and Bubba are determined to answer: who is the toughest tow truck around? An all new-adventure featuring your favorite World of Cars characters!

Up Your Nose and Out Your Ear
Pacific Comics Club Presents Flash Gordon

description:
The march toward TRINITY WAR begins with part one of “WORLD’S MOST DANGEROUS”!

Green Lantern! Green Arrow! Catwoman! Katana! Vibe! Hawkman! Stargirl! They aren’t the world’s greatest super heroes—they’re the most dangerous! But why does a team like the JLA need to exist? What is their ultimate mission? And who is pulling the strings?

The story opens five years ago with Professor Ivo and a mysterious figure in the shadows. It then quickly turns to today and a shadowy figure running from what looks like Batman, Wonder Woman and Superman but, they don't seem themselves. The story then turns to Amanda Waller and Steve Trevor building the roster for the new Justice League of America with flash-fowards of each member as they appear currently. Waller already knows how to get them on her team by controlling them.

As they go through the seven members of the team it is revealed that they believe these are the best team to take out the big seven Justice League is need be (Their big seven has Cyborg instead of Martian Manhunter) We also find out that the mysterious figure running away from Batman, Wonder Woman and Superman is none other than Green Arrow. Unfortunately, he bleeds to death only being able to tell Steve Trevor the groups name the Secret Society.

Notes:

The cover is an homage to the raising of the flag at Iwo Jima.

The end of the comic has a Channel 52 News Team segment.
name: World's Most Dangerous, Chapter One

description:
No, that’s not a typo. Vibe stars in his own ongoing monthly title, starting with this debut issue cowritten by GEOFF JOHNS!

One of the most unlikely members of the Justice League of America ever will soon discover he’s one of the most powerful individuals on Earth. But how did Vibe get his abilities? What is the cost to them? And why does the JLA want him on the team so desperately?

Plus: We’ve seen the Red Room and the Black Room, but what is...the Circus?
name: Not-So-Secret Origin

description:
The epic, full-length conclusion to “THRONE OF ATLANTIS” hits as Aquaman and the League make a sinister discovery that changes both the outcome of the war and the future of the Justice League!

What is THE GRID—and what does it mean to expanding the Justice League?

Plot

This story starts with a Flashback to Amnesty Bay and Aquaman remembers the worse storm in Amnesty Bay history which frightened Tom Curry. Aquaman's Dad fears that the Atlanteans are after young Arthur. The scene then switches back to the Watchtower, where the JLA check on Dr. Shin. Aquaman feels responsible for the War but Batman reminds him that he did not kill anyone and he did not sink the cities.
name: Throne of Atlantis, Chapter Five

description:
Dick Grayson’s life lies in ruins in the wake of the events surrounding “DEATH OF THE FAMILY”!

Is his career as Nightwing over? Where will he go now?

Will the voice of reason come from Damian Wayne?
name: The Long Week

description:
In the wake of “DEATH OF THE FAMILY,” Bruce Wayne confronts Jason Todd!

You DO NOT want to miss this!
name: Don't Let the Door Hit You on Your Way Out

description:
The Birds are trapped fighting Basilisk—in total darkness!

Something strange is happening to Black Canary…and only one man can be responsible. But Kurt Lance died years ago—right?
name: Heart Stopper

description:
It’s the massive conclusion to the current storyline as Batwoman and Wonder Woman struggle to defeat Medusa and a horde of villains!

Don’t miss the start of a surprising new status quo for Batwoman!
name: World's Finest, Part V: Mercy
